24/02/2011
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Army Chiefs of Staff of the Adriatic Charter member states will hold talks Thursday (February 24th) in Podgorica on possible joint participation of their forces in the ISAF mission in Afghanistan, to train Afghan army and police.
The meeting will bring together representatives of the A5 countries -- Montenegro, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Croatia, Macedonia, Albania -- as well as the US.
(RTCG, Mina, Radio Free Europe - 24/02/11)
